{{unreferenced|date=June 2009|bot=yes}}
[[Image:Baseballpositions.png|280px|right]]
There are 9 '''fielding positions''' in [[baseball]]. Each [[Baseball scorekeeping#Defensive positions|position]] conventionally has an associated number, which is used [[official scorer|to score]] [[putout]]s: 1 ([[pitcher]]), 2 ([[catcher]]), 3 ([[first baseman]]), 4 ([[second baseman]]), 5 ([[third baseman]]), 6 ([[shortstop]]), 7 ([[outfielder|left fielder]]), 8 ([[outfielder|center fielder]]), and 9 ([[outfielder|right fielder]]).  For example:
*If the third baseman fields a ball and throws it to first, it is recorded as a 5–3 [[out (baseball)|out]].
*A [[double play]] where the second baseman fields, throws to the shortstop covering second base, who throws to the 1st baseman is recorded as a 4–6–3 double play.

